   {:e #blake3 "9465095f9d35630c70ca61823a5d7b4ad2a4b58bab58dcf5ef0dd6d4d559d86d" :a :task/description :v "CONTEXT: Comprehensive test suite for ALL S045-QUALITY defect remediations: S045-Q1-REV (acquisition-aligned scoring), S045-Q2 (latest-wins), S045-Q3 (cross-type winner), S045-Q4 (scan merge), S045-Q5 (dead arm). 7 new tests total.\n\nUNIT TESTS:\n\n1. test_frontier_scores_bounded_zero_one (Q1-REV property P3):\n   - Property: ALL frontier candidate scores are in [0.0, 1.0] regardless of store state.\n   - Setup: Store with extreme values — 100 packages, 50 observations, variance at SPLIT_THRESHOLD.\n   - For EACH candidate returned by explore_candidates, deepen_candidates, bridge_candidates:\n     assert!(score >= 0.0 && score <= 1.0, 'score {score} out of bounds for {kind}');\n   - Failure diagnostic: Log each candidate with kind, raw inputs, and computed score formula.\n\n2. test_frontier_deepen_saturated (Q1-REV property P2 — monotonicity):\n   - Property: Higher variance produces higher score. More members produce higher score.\n   - Setup: Two concepts with same member count but different variance.\n   - Assert: higher_variance_concept.score > lower_variance_concept.score.\n   - Then: Two concepts with same variance but different member counts.\n   - Assert: higher_count_concept.score > lower_count_concept.score.\n   - Failure diagnostic: Log both concepts' variance, member_count, and computed scores.\n\n3. test_frontier_commensurable (Q1-REV — the critical test):\n   - Property: Deepen with variance=SPLIT_THRESHOLD and member_count=total_observations scores ~1.0.\n     Explore with connections=total_packages scores ~1.0. They compete fairly.\n   - Setup: Store with ONE concept (variance=0.5, 10 members, 10 total observations) and ONE unexplored package connected to all 5 explored packages (connections=5, total=5).\n   - Assert: both Deepen score and Explore score are in [0.8, 1.0].\n   - Assert: the winner is determined by which has genuinely higher E[delta-F(S)], not by scale artifacts.\n   - Failure diagnostic: Log ALL candidates with kind, inputs, and score showing the algebra.\n\n4. test_assign_to_concepts_latest_wins (Q2 — DEFECT-004):\n   - Property: In append-only store with two :concept/embedding assertions for same entity, the later is used.\n   - Setup: store_with_schema(), add concept with embedding A at tx=10, embedding B at tx=11.\n   - Assert: observation matching B has higher similarity than one matching A.\n   - Failure diagnostic: Log both embeddings (as first 5 dimensions), both cosine similarities.\n\n5. test_frontier_all_three_candidates (Q3 — DEFECT-005):\n   - Property: When all 3 candidate types return results, the winning kind has the highest E[delta-F(S)].\n   - Setup: Store with Explore (3 connections / 10 packages = 0.3), Deepen (variance=0.4/0.5 * 5/10 = 0.4), Bridge (1.0 * 8/20 = 0.4). Deepen and Bridge should be close.\n   - Expose candidates via a new frontier_candidates() helper that returns the full Vec before winner selection.\n   - Assert: result.kind matches the type with max score. Assert all 3 kinds present.\n   - Failure diagnostic: Log complete candidate list sorted by score.\n\n6. test_co_occurrence_single_scan_equivalence (Q4 correctness guard):\n   - Property: Merged single-scan co_occurrence_matrix produces identical results to the old two-scan version.\n   - Setup: Store with 3 concepts, 20 observations, mixed membership.\n   - Run co_occurrence_matrix, verify identical output to test_co_occurrence_matrix_coupled baseline.\n   - This is a regression guard, not a new capability test.\n   - Failure diagnostic: Log both outputs side by side showing any divergence.\n\n7. test_assign_to_concepts_no_uncategorized_in_vec (Q5 verification):\n   - Property: assign_to_concepts NEVER returns a vec containing ConceptAssignment::Uncategorized.\n   - Setup: proptest with random observation embeddings.\n   - For each result vec, assert no element matches Uncategorized.\n   - Failure diagnostic: Log the observation embedding and threshold that produced an Uncategorized in the vec.\n\nE2E REGRESSION GATE:\n- cargo test -p braid-kernel --lib concept:: (all 78+ existing + 7 new pass)\n- cargo test -p braid-kernel --lib routing:: (all routing tests pass)\n- ./scripts/e2e_frontier_steering.sh (all 7 E2E checks pass)\n- cargo clippy --all-targets -- -D warnings\n\nDEPENDS-ON: S045-Q1-REV (t-43e3a55b), S045-Q2 (t-62eb3212)." :op :assert}
